<dl id="n25082g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25082g">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25082g"> 82(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> smallarms</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On riding over the summit of the acclivity, the allies were received with so hot a fire from the French artillery and <mark>small arms</mark>, that at first the cavalry recoiled, but without abandoning the high ground. <small> Edward Creasy, <a name="ECFD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ECFD"><cite title="source">The Fifteen Decisive Battles of the World</cite></a> (1915) 311</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14050l" href="c14all.htm#c14050l">VI.C.14:050(l)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
